column5: seen this one before i love how stunned the goalie looks
I'd never seen it Joe.....spectacular shot!
I'm kinda disappointed!... I thought Rocket the goat ate a puck or something.

I have seen a guy do that duing a game.  Let me tell you, when you are on D and the guy is coming in with the puck starts to spin like that you start to watch him and not the puck. Great trick for a 9-year old though.
A 9yr old playing with 12yr olds, kinda sounds like a kid from Brantford.
ive seen this before crazy sick tho

I remember Jason Blake doing something similar during a shootout last season, trouble is, if you are successful you are a hero, if you flub it , you look like a idiot. Gotta admit though , the kids has hands for a 9 year old.
Blake's goal was just a spinorama... he didn't actually lift the puck up off the ice... he used that move twice last year.
Quick,Burk,sign him.  Wrong era.LOL For those that caught my mistake.
Thats wicked...I am not sure how he did it even after the 12th time I watched it.   Art
The kid's got great talent    and it's one slick move he was able to do for a  9 year old Wouldn't surprise me if we see him in the NHL..... he's got great potential!!! Leechman
